text: at the timestamp 22.07, we will not divide by 2, the value in z-table gives the area at left of the value so 1-0.99111 will give all the area to left of +2.307(which will include the area to the left of -2.307 too). Therefore no need to half, as the sum of both the areas + 0.9911 will be greater than 1, please notice that 2x0.008899 + 0.9111 = 1.008899, i.e., 0.0088 greater than 1, as we have added the shaded area to the left of mean twice.

author: @DharmendraKumar-DS
text: I think:  The area for the z-score of 2.307 = 0.9828 , which is the area including the confidence interval + left rejection region.   Therefore, the area of the both rejection region of left and right will be equal which is 1-0.9828 = 0.0172. Which means:  Area of left rejection  region = 0.0172,  Area of right rejection region = 0.0172  The area of the confidence interval will be 1-(2x0.0172) = 0.9656.   The P-Value will be 2x0.0172 = 0.0344.
